  • Orange wire harnesses and connectors indicate high-voltage circuits. To prevent electric shock, always follow the procedure described in the repair manual.

  • To prevent electric shock, wear insulated gloves when working on wire harnesses and components of the high voltage system.

PROCEDURE

1. PRECAUTION

NOTICE:

After turning the power switch off, waiting time may be required before disconnecting the cable from the negative (-) auxiliary battery terminal. Therefore, make sure to read the disconnecting the cable from the negative (-) auxiliary battery terminal notices before proceeding with work.

Click here

2. REMOVE SERVICE PLUG GRIP

Click here

3. REMOVE REAR NO. 1 FLOOR BOARD

Click here

4. REMOVE REAR DECK FLOOR BOX

Click here

5. REMOVE INVERTER TERMINAL COVER

CAUTION:

Be sure to wear insulated gloves.

(a) Remove the 5 bolts and inverter terminal cover from the rear hybrid motor control inverter assembly.

NOTICE:

  • Make sure to pull the inverter terminal cover straight out, as a connector is connected to the inside of the inverter terminal cover.
  • Do not touch the waterproof seal of the inverter terminal cover.
  • Do not allow any foreign matter or water to enter the rear hybrid motor control inverter assembly.
  • Make sure that the interlock is installed to the inverter terminal cover.

*a

Interlock

*b

Waterproof Seal

6. CHECK TERMINAL VOLTAGE

CAUTION:

Be sure to wear insulated gloves.

NOTICE:

  • Do not allow any foreign matter or water to enter the rear hybrid motor control inverter assembly.
  • Do not use A terminal for measurement.

(a) Using a voltmeter, measure the voltage between the terminals of the 2 phase connectors.

Standard Voltage:

0 V

HINT:

Use a measuring range of DC 750 V or more on the voltmeter.

7. DISCONNECT HV FLOOR UNDER WIRE

CAUTION:

Be sure to wear insulated gloves.

(a) Using an insulated tool, remove the 4 bolts and disconnect the HV floor under wire from the rear hybrid motor control inverter assembly.

NOTICE:

  • Do not allow any foreign matter or water to enter the rear hybrid motor control inverter assembly.
  • Do not touch the waterproof seal or terminals of the HV floor under wire.
  • Do not damage the terminals, connector housing or rear hybrid motor control inverter assembly during disconnection.
  • Insulate the disconnected terminals with insulating tape.

*a

Waterproof Seal

8. DISCONNECT HV BATTERY PACK WIRE

CAUTION:

Be sure to wear insulated gloves.

(a) Using an insulated tool, remove the 4 bolts and disconnect the HV battery pack wire from the rear hybrid motor control inverter assembly.

NOTICE:

  • Do not allow any foreign matter or water to enter the rear hybrid motor control inverter assembly.
  • Do not touch the waterproof seal or terminals of theHV battery pack wire.
  • Do not damage the terminals, connector housing or rear hybrid motor control inverter assembly during disconnection.
  • Insulate the disconnected terminals with insulating tape.
  • Make sure to pull the HV battery pack wire straight out, as a connector is connected to the inside of the inverter terminal cover.

*a

Interlock

*b

Waterproof Seal

9. DISCONNECT REAR TRACTION MOTOR CABLE

CAUTION:

Be sure to wear insulated gloves.

(a) Using an insulated tool, remove the 5 bolts and disconnect the rear traction motor cable from the rear hybrid motor control inverter assembly.

NOTICE:

  • Do not allow any foreign matter or water to enter the rear hybrid motor control inverter assembly.
  • Do not touch the waterproof seal or terminals of the rear traction motor cable.
  • Do not damage the terminals, connector housing or rear hybrid motor control inverter assembly during disconnection.
  • Insulate the disconnected terminals with insulating tape.
  • Make sure to pull the rear traction motor cable out, as a connector is connected to the inside of the inverter terminal cover.

*a

Waterproof Seal

10. TEMPORARILY INSTALL INVERTER TERMINAL COVER

CAUTION:

Be sure to wear insulated gloves.

(a) Temporarily install the inverter terminal cover with the 5 bolts.

NOTICE:

Do not touch the waterproof seal of the inverter terminal cover.

11. REMOVE REAR HYBRID MOTOR CONTROL INVERTER ASSEMBLY

CAUTION:

Be sure to wear insulated gloves.

(a) Disconnect the 2 rear hybrid motor control inverter assembly connectors.

NOTICE:

  • Do not touch the waterproof seal or terminals of the connector.
  • Do not damage the terminals, connector housing or rear hybrid motor control inverter assembly during disconnection.
  • Cover the hole where the cable was connected with tape (non-residue type) or equivalent to prevent entry of foreign matter.
  • Do not allow any foreign matter or water to enter therear hybrid motor control inverter assembly.
  • Insulate the disconnected terminals with insulating tape.
  • To prevent damage due to staticelectricity, do not touch the terminals of the disconnected connectors.

(b) Remove the 3 bolts and rear hybrid motor control inverter assembly.

NOTICE:

  • Do not damage the terminals, connector housing or rear hybrid motor control inverter assembly during disconnection.
  • Cover the hole where the cable was connected with tape (non-residue type) or equivalent to prevent entry of foreign matter.
  • Do not allow any foreign matter or water to enter the rear hybrid motor control inverter assembly.
  • Insulate the disconnected terminals with insulating tape.
  • To prevent damage due to staticelectricity, do not touch the terminals of the disconnected connectors.

12. REMOVE HV INVERTER COOLING COVER

CAUTION:

Be sure to wear insulated gloves.

HINT:

Perform this procedure only when replacement of the HV inverter cooling fan is necessary.

(a) Using a T25 "TORX" socket wrench, remove the 4 bolts and HV inverter cooling cover from the rear hybrid motor control inverter assembly.

13. REMOVE HV INVERTER COOLING FAN

CAUTION:

Be sure to wear insulated gloves.

HINT:

Perform this procedure only when replacement of the HV inverter cooling fan is necessary.

(a) Disconnect the rear hybrid motor control inverter assembly.

(b) Disengage the clamp.

(c) Disengage the 2 guides.

(d) Using a T20 "TORX" socket wrench, remove the 3 bolts and HV inverter cooling fan from the rear hybrid motor control inverter assembly.
